> All I have is:
> 
> TED.history
> TEDSCREEN
> TEDSPORT
> TEDSSCREEN
> 
> This could be the problem?

Get and install the updates David recommended - then go into the
SYS:prefs/Env-archive/ directory and delete anything to do with ted and the
debugger.

To be completely safe, you can also go into RAM:ENV/ and delete them there
as well.

After rebooting, ted and the debugger will just use their defaults until you
save some new settings, it's just that they sometimes mess up when trying
to use old preference files.

Later...
-- 
When choosing between two evils,
always try the one you have never tried before.

