@NODE "Mail_191" "Re: Enforcer hits"
From: Curt Esser <camge@ix.netcom.com>
Date: Thu, 05 Aug 1999 07:46:06 -0500
Subject: Re: Enforcer hits
X-UIDL: fd9be7a06447993a68149a476f882295

Hi Tony

On 04-Aug-99, Tony Rolfe wrote:
> Can anyone explain why the Window statement at the end of this program
> has enforcer hits.

Yes, it is the $80 in the window flags you are using.

If I substitute this:
Window 0,0,0,Screen_Width,Screen_Height,$1000|$800|$100,"",1,2

It runs fine - no hits.

What is the $80 in your flags?  I don't find it in the manual, and it is the
one that causes the hits.

Later...
-- 


