Hi Mathias
On the 19-Aug-99 you said something about Re: HEX problems (again, for the third time this year!) so now I am going to offer a witty retort (well maybe :)

> Would you give more details  ? How do you read, and convert, and print
> the byte ?

I FileSeek to the position of it, and then read it in using edit$ and
convert it to an integer it hink using Cvi. Like this

FileSeek 0,1425:tmp$=Edit$(2):skills(1)=Cvi(tmp$)

Note that 1425 is a made up offset.

Then it returns 0 instead of 10.

And I use OpenFile, not ReadFIle or WriteFile
