@NODE "Mail_290" "Indirect Gosub"
From: "Tony Rolfe" <edgewater@shoalhaven.net.au>
Organization: Edgewater Motel, Burrill Lake, NSW 2539 Australia
Date: 10 Aug 99 09:50:20 +1000
Subject: Indirect Gosub
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: 32f291717916ad7922497cb10a3eb4a6

Hi,

Is there any way to store the address of a routine in a variable and
then gosub the routine based on the variable?   

Something like:

Routine_Address.l = &Routine1
gosub main_routine

Routine_Address = &Routine2
gosub main_routine

end

main_routine
...
gosub <<routine whose address is contained in>>Routine_Address
...
return
Routine1
...
return
Routine2
...
return

I don't want to do an On... Gosub, because that means I have to change
the main routine each time I add a new calling routine.   

Thanks in advance

-- 
Tony Rolfe
Amiga 2000, 68030/25, 1+4Mb
www.shoalhaven.net.au/edgewater

