Date: 24 Aug 99 19:13:07 +1000
Subject: Memory Problem (fixed)
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: 2e89eba74bafe6c053a7bbe6b741b57d

The cause of my memory problems was a patch called MemSpeed which slowed my system down
by a factor of 4.  Anyone who is using it may want to do a sysinfo speed test
with and without it.

I was lucky enough to win a copy of WB3.5 pre-release.   If anyone
wants info on this, let me know & I'll post here or privately,
depending on what the group thinks


