Date: Tue, 24 Aug 1999 11:39:09 -0000
	charset="iso-8859-2"
Encoding: 7bit
X-UIDL: 474b78c773266f7202a2bd2128c90c7e

I've trouble with NCS v1.90 :-(
Look at the modified a bit Fred's example:

; *********************************************************
;                     Example 2
;           Open a Workbench like screen...
; *********************************************************

WBStartup
NInitScreen 1
NInitWindow 0
TgList.l = NInitTagList(2)

If NWbToScreen(1)
  NResetTagList #SA_LikeWorkbench , 1
  If NScreen(0, NScreenWidth, NScreenHeight, NScreenDepth, TgList)
    NResetTagList #WA_CustomScreen , NScreenID
    NWindow 0, 0, NSBarHeight+1, 300, 200, TgList
  Else
    NPrint "Unable to open this screen !"
  EndIf
Else
  NPrint "Can't lock the WBScreen"
EndIf
NPrint "Left mouse button to quit."
NMouseWait
NCloseScreen(0)
zz=Request("Simple requester","Check if the opened screen|is now
closed...","Click me")
End

After the END instruction all resources are freed but when I WANT to close
NCS screen I can't do that. The screen is still opened :-(
I'm not sure if I've made a mistake or it is a bug inside the NCS v1.90. Any
ideas?

Chris, eteacher@amiga.org.pl



