On Wed, 18 Aug 1999 18:27:59 +0100 James L Boyd said:
> Hi all, 
> 
> I need help on what should be a really simple mathematical problem...
> 
> How do I find what percentage one number is of another?
> 
> For example, how would I find x here :
> 
> The number 14 is x% of 76.
> 
I always do x = 14 x 10000 / 76 

which gives the answer 100 times bigger than needed and then I stuff a
decimal point two characters from the right.

Of course, that is only needed coz I'm using long variables.   If you
are using floats, just do x = 14 x 100 / 76.

Hope that helps


