> PPC programs now and easily compiling for the NG later... Sounds great -
> and could make PB a bestseller :-).

Going by what Fred has said, the editor is independent of the final
compilation.  The ASM code is taken from different modules and passed to an
ASM compiler.  This would mean that the editor/pre-compiler could run on
the Classic Amiga Emulation that should be in the AmigaNG machine, all it
would take would be for someone to make the neccessary modules for the
final compilation. I think. Maybe. :)

