Not with normal Blitz commands. I'm sure Mildred can do it but you need a
table setup so your transparent colours are correct, therefore your palette
needs to be well thought out.

I've been doing this with 16Bit lately and it's a joy to work
with...no palette problems at all and perfect transparencies and lighting
effects.

The code for my work is in C++ but it shouldn't be too hard to do it in
Blitz. 16Bit for Blitz....one of my MANY things I've got to
do/finish....well sometime maybe ;)

